<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/watchos-26/">watchOS 26</a> includes a feature that lets you know if you're using an Apple Watch charger that is not optimized for the fastest charging speeds.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/09/watchos-26-slow-charger.jpg" alt="" width="1132" height="637" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1019778" /><br/>
According to a <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/122696">new Apple support document</a>, if your Apple Watch detects a charging experience that could be improved, a Slow Charger message will be displayed in the Battery section of the Settings app. Instances of slow charging are shown in orange, while fast charging speeds are displayed in green.<br/>
<br/>
Apple says that the Slow Charger warning simply means that you could get faster charging speeds with a higher-wattage charger, and it does not mean there is something wrong with a slower charger.<br/>
<br/>
Apple recommends a USB-C Power Delivery charger and the USB-C Apple Watch Magnetic Charging Cable that came with the watch for the fastest charging.<br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/09/16/watchos-26-slow-charger-warnings/">Apple Watch Gets Slow Charger Warnings in watchOS 26</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/apple-watch-gets-slow-charger-warnings-in-watchos-26.2466114/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>